Alter table:

1.
Qn:
Add columns 'created_at' and 'updated_at' to the tables marks, students and medals.

Ans:
alter table marks add column created_at timestamp, add column updated_at timestamp;

alter table students add column created_at timestamp, add column updated_at timestamp;

alter table medals add column created_at timestamp, add column updated_at timestamp;

2.
Qn:
Replace the null values in quarterly, half_yearly and annual columns with 0 and make those columns as not nullable.

Ans:
update marks set quarterly = case when quarterly is null then 0 else quarterly end, half_yearly = case when half_yearly is null then 0 else half_yearly end, annual = case when annual is null then 0 else annual end;

alter table marks modify column quarterly int not null, modify column half_yearly int not null, modify column annual int not null;


Insert and update:

3.
Questions:
While inserting the value of updated_at & created_at should be the current time
While updating the value of updated_at alone should be the time of update

Ans:
Alter table marks modify column created_at timestamp default now() , modify column updated_at timestamp default now() on update now();

Alter table students modify column created_at timestamp default now(), modify column updated_at timestamp default now on update now();

Alter table medals modify column created_at timestamp default now(), modify column updated_at timestamp default now() on update now();